      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3, a pure driver's machine powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit features six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Vanos system, recently serviced to ensure optimal variable valve timing. The 6-speed manual transmission provides tactile engagement, paired with a variable M differential lock for superior traction. Crucially, the rear subframe has been reinforced to address common chassis fatigue, and the suspension has been refreshed with polyurethane bushings for sharpened turn-in response. While the exterior shows honest patina from spirited driving, the powertrain remains robust with consistent compression across all cylinders. This is a high-performance specimen optimized for the curves, free of the common mechanical gremlins associated with neglected E46 platforms.",
